<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
Hardened Runtime entitlements for the bundled Python sidecar.

Empirically reduced during Track C C0 (18 Apr 2026) from v0.1's full set.

Load-bearing: ONLY com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation.
  Reason: the outer binary is ad-hoc signed (Team ID = "-"); the bundled
  Python.framework and every .so file are ad-hoc signed with different
  identifiers. Library validation otherwise blocks dlopen with
  "mapping process and mapped file have different Team IDs".

NOT needed for serve-only scope (confirmed by empty-entitlement test,
Python 3.12 + mlx_whisper, Apr 2026):
  - cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory: CPython 3.12 does not use W+X.
  - cs.allow-jit: ctranslate2 is excluded; MLX uses Metal GPU kernels, not CPU JIT.
  - cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables: not required for serve.

If a future addition needs any of the above, document the trigger here.
App Sandbox + user-facing entitlements (files, network, bookmarks)
are Track A's concern — the sidecar will add com.apple.security.inherit
at that point so the parent's sandbox applies.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
